Financial Crime Data Scientist based out of Milton Keynes.
We’re shaping the way we work through innovation, cutting-edge technology, collaboration and the freedom to explore new ideas. To succeed in this role, you will be responsible for:
• Collaborate with internal stakeholders across Transaction Monitoring product teams, Compliance Controls, and Business Risk, while partnering closely with technical delivery teams (CIO and CDO functions).
• Design, write, test, and maintain production-quality code; develop, experiment with, and evaluate both rule-based and AI-driven algorithms and models.
• Enhance methodologies by developing new data sources, testing model improvements, fine-tuning parameters, and ensuring comprehensive and compliant model documentation.
• Deliver analytical insights into alert generation performance, assess the impact of country risk changes, support remediation activities for historical issues, and contribute to executive reporting with transaction monitoring performance analytics across key financial crime systems and applications (e.g., NetReveal, ThetaRay).
• Communicate effectively with business stakeholders and leadership at all levels of technical expertise, providing education, insights, and actionable recommendations.

WHAT YOU’LL BRING
Our people are our greatest strength. Every individual contributes unique perspectives that make us stronger as a team and as an organisation. We’re enabling teams to go beyond by valuing who they are and empowering what they bring.
The following requirements represent the knowledge, skills, and abilities essential for success in this role. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.
Professional Experience 
• Expert proficiency in Python and SQL within a Big Data environment. (Required)
• Extensive experience in designing, implementing, and calibrating financial crime detection models using rule-based, supervised, and unsupervised machine learning techniques. (Required)
• Strong analytical experience in compliance-related domains, such as financial crime, fraud, or regulatory compliance. (Preferred)
Education
• High level degree in a scientific/numerical discipline – Bsc, MSc, PhD (Preferred)

Hard Skills
• Expert proficiency in Python and SQL. (Required)
• Proven experience with distributed computational frameworks, including AWS, Impala, Hive, Hadoop, and Spark. (Required)
• Solid understanding of financial market instruments. (Preferred)
• Experience in financial crime controls and related compliance systems. (Preferred)
Soft Skills
• Proficient in source control and version management, with experience using GitHub and Gluon, and strong knowledge of unit testing practices. (Preferred)
• Analytical and strategic problem-solver, capable of working independently with minimal supervision. (Required)
• Strong communicator, able to convey complex technical concepts clearly and succinctly to non-technical audiences. (Required)

